OL,3,CEqualities watchdog urges government
OL,4,Cto speed up trans guidance
OL,6,FSpeaking on behalf of TACC and TEN,
OL,7,FMrs. Duerinckx wrote that statements
OL,8,Fmade by Supreme Court Justice, Lord
OL,9,FHodge, amounted to an admission "that
OL,10,Fthe effect of the (Supreme Court
OL,11,Fruling) was that trans people had
OL,12,Fnever had the rights they were led to
OL,13,Fbelieve by the State to have had."
OL,15,FThey are asking the international
OL,16,Fcourt to consider whether the UK is
OL,17,Fstill meeting equality obligations in
OL,18,Fthe wake of April's Supreme Court
OL,19,Fruling.
